#### 6. No Error Handling Middleware (OWASP A05 – Security Misconfiguration)
Unhandled errors in Express will produce a default stack trace response that **leaks internal implementation details** (file paths, module names, line numbers) to the client.

**Fix:** Add a global error handler as the **last** middleware:
```js
// Generic error handler - must have 4 arguments
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err); // Log full error server-side only
