The server listens on plain HTTP port 3000 with no redirect to HTTPS. All data (including any future auth tokens) is transmitted in plaintext.

**Fix:** In production, terminate TLS at the load balancer/reverse proxy (e.g., nginx, AWS ALB) and enforce HTTPS redirects. If running standalone:
